const headHtml = "<title>Farming Progression Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based farming progression guide for Hypixel SkyBlock covering Garden unlocks, visitors, copper, plot setup, early tools and the upgrades worth buying first.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/farming-progression-guide-2026\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/farming-progression-guide-2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Farming Progression Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Build a sensible Garden progression path without overspending on upgrades your account is not ready to exploit yet.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"Farming Progression Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\",\n        \"description\": \"Expert based guide to farming progression and Garden income in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-02-09\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"\n        },\n        \"publisher\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"\n        },\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/farming-progression-guide-2026\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-02-09 • Farming</a>\n          <h1>Farming Progression Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Farming keeps attracting players for a simple reason: it offers one of the cleanest low-stress progression paths in the game. But strong farming guides are not just crop lists. They are progression maps. Garden unlocks, visitor flow, copper, plot layout and tool timing all matter, and if you skip that structure you can burn millions on convenience long before your account can turn those purchases into real income.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> Xentyl's 2026 farming progression coverage, especially the Garden unlock sequence, visitor handling, plot setup and crop-tool timing.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>Garden access is the real beginning</h2>\n          <p>The cleanest farming advice in current creator coverage is to treat the Garden as your first true milestone, not a side activity. Once the Garden is open, farming becomes a system with visitors, copper, plot management and dedicated progression rather than random island harvesting.</p>\n          <p>That matters for money because the Garden compounds. Visitors push progress forward, copper unlocks better tools and upgrades, and better plot structure turns the same playtime into better output.</p>\n\n          <h2>Do not overspend on the wrong upgrades</h2>\n          <p>One of the best practical warnings in farming guides is that not every visible system deserves your coins early. The composter can become useful later, but early overinvestment there often does less for your income than cleaner plots, better crop tools or stronger visitor handling. A good progression guide protects you from expensive premature upgrades.</p>\n          <p>The efficient early path is usually simple: unlock the Garden, stabilize your farm layout, improve the tools that directly raise output, and only then start layering on more expensive convenience systems.</p>\n\n          <h2>Visitors and copper are part of the money method</h2>\n          <p>Farming is easy to misread if you only think in harvested crop value. Visitors and copper are part of the progression economy, not optional side flavor. The sooner you respect that, the sooner farming starts looking like a full account builder instead of a single crop loop.</p>\n          <p>Live price tools still matter here. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a> helps with crop-side pricing, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">top movers</a> catches sudden Garden-material swings, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz</a> gives a broader trend lens, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a> helps check whether supporting materials are getting too expensive to justify a route shift.</p>\n\n          <h2>Build the base first, specialize later</h2>\n          <p>This page is the umbrella farming guide for the series. Later pages like pest farming or melon versus wheat only make sense if your base Garden progression is already stable. If you jump into niche farming discussions before the platform is ready, you are optimizing noise instead of income.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/pest-farming-guide-2026\">Pest Farming Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/melon-vs-wheat-farming\">Melon vs Wheat Farming Economics</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\">Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz trends</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/bazaar-flipping\">BazaarPro bazaar flipping</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Players looking for a low-stress progression path that can grow into a serious income stream without immediate late-game spending.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Source videos</h3>\n            <p>Xentyl is the backbone here because his farming progression coverage treats the Garden as an ordered system instead of a crop recommendation.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
